===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|boot|lang=enm}}, {{term|bot|lang=enm}}, {{term|boet|lang=enm}}, {{term|boyt||boat|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|bāt||boat}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*baitaz}}, {{term/t|gem-pro|*baitą||boat, small ship}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*bheid-||to break, split}}. Cognate with {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|beit||boat|lang=non}}.

{{etyl|non|-}} {{term|bátr|bātr|lang=non}} (whence {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|bátur|lang=is}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|båt|lang=no}}),  {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|boot|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Boot|lang=de}}, {{etyl|oc|-}} {{term|batèl|lang=oc}} and {{etyl|fr|-}} {{term|bateau|lang=fr}} are all ultimately borrowings from the {{etyl|ang|-}} word.

